This paper uses natural language processing techniques to analyze a corpus of tweets to discover basic emotion sets. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the sub-category of Computational Linguistics (cs.CL). Additionally, the paper uses Latent Semantic Clustering (LSC), which is a machine learning technique, making it relevant to the sub-categories of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of data visualization to analyze emotions, which could fall under the sub-category of Cybernetics (cs.CY). Finally, the paper uses statistical analysis to determine the optimal basic emotion set, which could be relevant to the sub-category of Sound (cs.SD) as it involves analyzing and processing audio data.
